<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRAN LEADER ASSAILS RIVAL SHIITE GROUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Iranian leader, in Tehran's strongest condemnation so far, said Friday that 
Iran is disgusted by the fighting between rival Shiite Muslim militias in 
Lebanon. 
</P>
<P>
Parliamentary Speaker Hashemi Rafsanjani said the pro-Iranian Hezbollah (Party 
of God) militia and the rival Syrian-backed Amal group "are both committing 
murder and the Islamic Republic is disgusted," the Iranian news agency IRNA 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
He told a mass prayer meeting in Tehran that the clashes are revolting. 
</P>
<P>
Tehran finances Hezbollah and praises it as the standard-bearer of true Islam 
in Lebanon. 
</P>
<P>
At least 116 people have been killed in the past two weeks in some of the worst 
fighting between Amal and Hezbollah in Beirut and southern Lebanon. 
</P>
