AMBASSADOR HOTEL CLOSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The site of the closed Ambassador Hotel -- favorably situated on the main 
street of Los Angeles and not far from the heart of downtown Los Angeles -- 
should remain an urban oasis. The setback of the hotel building and the garden 
areas provides agreeable relief. 
</P>
<P>
It has been said that, unlike some cities, such as London, Los Angeles has a 
paucity of green spaces. The suggestion for mixed use -- residential, 
commercial, and hotel -- sounds bad. Los Angeles already is built up just about 
to the hilt. 
</P>
<P>
I hope that the hotel can be preserved. If not, something else very special and 
equally meritorious, which retains the open space, should occupy the site. 
