<P>
HILLBILLY COLUMN IS ENTERTAINING, BUT ALSO POINTS UP A PROBLEM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On one hand, I found Mike Downey's column of Jan. 1 creative and entertaining. 
On the other hand, I was aghast to find that he included phrases like "mixing 
up another batch of moonshine," "whut in tarnation," "I ain't never seen no 
television," "out thar," "whole danged country," "old jalopy," and "we's all 
kin." 
</P>
<P>
Even though my family has lived in Southern California for more than 20 years, 
we still have to laugh about the ignorance of some people here (and all over 
the country) about West Virginia. When we tell people we used to live in 
Parkersburg, West Va., they ask, "Is that close to Richmond?" They don't even 
know there is a state of West Virginia. And they think hillbillies look stupid? 
