<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORKING FOR JUSTICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The irony of "Working Girl" strikes a nerve ("Griffith Fits Glass Slipper as a 
'Working Girl' Cinderella," Dec. 2). 
</P>
<P>
Here's a fantasy film about a woman who's scrambling to find justice in the 
corporate world. In the end, she receives justice. 
</P>
<P>
But catch the credits that appear on the screen: Melanie Griffith gets third 
billing, behind Harrison Ford and Sigourney Weaver. Third billing for a film 
that Griffith clearly carried, a film that relied on her role to push the box 
office. 
</P>
<P>
C'mon, Hollywood. C'mon, 20th Century Fox. That's corporate injustice! 
</P>
<P>
NEIL EGLASH 
</P>
<P>
and F. DAVID RENNIE 
</P>
<P>
Studio City 
</P>
