<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL SOCCER; 
</P>
<P>
AGOURA GIRLS SET RECORD WITH 30TH WIN IN A ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Agoura High girls' soccer team set a Southern Section record Friday with 
its 30th consecutive win as the Chargers crushed Calabasas, 9-0, in a Frontier 
League match at Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura (15-0, 3-0 in league play), the Southern Section 2-A Division champion 
the past 3 years, has not been held to a tie since the middle of last season 
and is unbeaten in 66 consecutive matches. 
</P>
<P>
Heidi Walters and Vanessa Martin each scored 2 goals to lead Friday's assault. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 4, Calabasas 0 -- The Chargers, ranked No. 1 in the Southern Section 1-A 
Division, scored 3 second-half goals to break open a close Frontier League 
match at Agoura. The win was Agoura's 11th in a row. 
</P>
<P>
Four players -- Dominic Zapata, Eric Pratts, Matt Freedman and Tim Ward -- 
scored for the Chargers (12-2-1, 3-0). 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade 3, Bell-Jeff 1 -- Goals by Brady Mitchell, Jorge Chavez and Greg 
Baumgartner lifted the Eagles in a San Fernando Valley League match. 
</P>
<P>
Simi Valley 3, Camarillo 1 -- Brian Weaver scored 2 first-half goals as the 
host Pioneers (16-2, 4-0) remained undefeated in Marmonte League play. 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 2, La Salle 0 -- Alex Woodhead scored 28 seconds into the San Fernando 
Valley League match and Marty Holly added a first-half goal as the Saracens 
improved to 6-7, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
Channel Islands 1, Royal 0 -- The Raiders scored 26 minutes into the Marmonte 
League match at Channel Islands and prevailed despite being outshot, 20-4. 
</P>
<P>
Hart 1, Muir 1 -- Rich Schwein scored with 15 minutes to play, allowing Muir 
(5-0-1) to remain unbeaten in the Foothill League. 
</P>
