<P>
CS NORTHRIDGE, CLIPPERS MEETING DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A meeting scheduled for Friday between Cal State Northridge administrators and 
officials from the Los Angeles Clippers professional basketball team has been 
postponed until later this month, said Eliott Minninberg, a CSUN administrative 
vice president. 
</P>
<P>
Minninberg cited a conflict of schedules for the change of plans. On the agenda 
were informal talks regarding the Clippers' use of an arena that has been 
proposed for construction on the Northridge campus. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier Friday, a group of Anaheim businessmen announced that they had offered 
Clipper owner Donald Sterling $30 million to move the team to Anaheim as soon 
as a 20,000-seat arena is completed. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
