<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; 
</P>
<P>
NAACP, CABLE AWARDS SHARE SPOTLIGHT WITH VARIETY OF VIEWS ON THE PRESIDENCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It's a weekend for awards and another friendly presidential farewell. 
</P>
<P>
The Rev. Jesse Jackson, Whitney Houston, Eddie Murphy and Clint Eastwood are 
among the big names participating in the 21st annual "NAACP Image Awards," 
tonight at 11:30 on Channels 4, 36 and 39. Taped last month at the Wiltern 
Theatre, the awards honor artistic excellence and the positive portrayal of 
minorities in television, films and recordings. 
</P>
<P>
Sunday, cable trots out its finest for the 10th Annual ACE Awards for 
excellence in cable-TV programming, airing live from the Wiltern at 6 p.m. on 
TBS, the Discovery Channel, Black Entertainment Television, the CBN Family 
Channel, FNN and TNT and at 9 p.m. on USA, Lifetime and Nickelodeon. "Night 
Court's" Harry Anderson hosts cable's answer to the Emmys. 
</P>
<P>
At 11 p.m. Sunday, Clifton Davis and Jackee host "The 10th Black Achievement 
Awards" on KHJ-TV Channel 9. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mike Wallace conducts a farewell interview with the President and 
the First Lady on Sunday at 7 p.m. on "60 Minutes." The talk with Ronald and 
Nancy Reagan, their final television appearance before leaving the White House 
next week, will cover a wide range of topics spanning the President's 
eight-year term. STEVE WEINSTEIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
