COFFIN CRUSHES HEARSE DRIVER IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COLD SPRING, Ky. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The driver of a hearse was crushed to death between the dashboard and a coffin 
in a head-on collision, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Jack Volkering, 59, of Ft. Wright, was returning from a funeral Mass on 
Wednesday when a car crossed the road and struck the hearse, Police Chief Gene 
Schweitzer said. 
</P>
<P>
The coffin broke through a metal holding post and struck Volkering in the back 
as the dashboard and steering wheel hit him in the chest, said Dr. Fred Stine, 
Campbell County coroner. 
</P>
<P>
Another hearse picked up the body in the coffin immediately after the accident 
and it was buried Thursday as scheduled, a funeral home spokesman said. 
