<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEXICO'S CLUB AMERICA SCORES 2-1 WIN OVER BAYERN MUNICH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AL PRESTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luis Alves scored one goal and set up another to give Mexico's Club America 
soccer team a 2-1 victory over Bayern Munich of West Germany in an exhibition 
match Friday night at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Alves' offensive play supported the goalkeeping of Adrian Chavez, who withstood 
a barrage of Bayern Munich shots to record 9 saves. 
</P>
<P>
Club America went ahead, 2-1, with 22 minutes left when Alves grounded a 
diagonal pass to Juan Hernandez, who broke away from the Bayern Munich defense 
to score. 
</P>
<P>
The match was played before an estimated crowd of 11,500 -- the largest to see 
a soccer match in Santa Ana sinc Dec. 4, 1987, when 11,700 watched an Olympic 
qualifying match between Mexico and Guyana. AL PRESTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
