<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE RALLIES IN FOURTH QUARTER, BEATS KENNEDY IN OVERTIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trailing by 11 points early in the fourth quarter, Garden Grove High School 
came back to send the game into overtime and upset Kennedy, 37-35, Friday in a 
Garden Grove League boys' basketball game at Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
Junior forward Chuck York, Garden Grove's first substitution of the game, went 
in with 6 minutes remaining and hit 2 3-point shots, the second one to tie the 
score, 35-35, with 19 seconds remaining. Kennedy's Mike Pettengill missed a 
shot at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
Senior guard Brian Tran hit a driving jump shot with 4 seconds remaining in 
overtime to give the Argonauts (3-11 overall, 2-3 in league play) the victory 
in front of about 500. Kennedy is 10-7, 3-2. 
</P>
<P>
In overtime, Kennedy won the tip and Tom Deep went to the line for a 1-and-1 
with 2:48 remaining. He missed the first shot and Garden Grove, which played a 
delay game throughout, worked the ball to set up Tran's shot. 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove's Joe Squyres, a junior, led all scorers with 15 points and hit 5 
of 6 free throws in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Barker, who led Kennedy with 10 points, got off a 26-foot shot at the end 
of overtime but missed. 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League games: 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica 64, Rancho Alamitos 50 -- Bill Maurer scored 14 points and had 12 
assists to lead Pacifica (10-3, 5-0) at home. Mike Maher had 18 points and 13 
rebounds for Pacifica. 
</P>
