<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: MEDICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Leslie Berkman, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mission Hospital Regional Medical Center this month will begin construction of 
an outpatient surgical center next to the hospital in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
The $3-million project, called the Mission Ambulatory SurgiCenter, is a joint 
venture between the hospital and members of the hospital's medical staff. 
</P>
<P>
The center will have five operating rooms and is expected to be open in 
November. "It is going to give more options to patients and physicians and 
ultimately lower costs for less complicated procedures by offering an 
alternative to hospital surgery," said Beth Groves, the hospital's community 
relations coordinator. 
</P>
</TEXT>
