</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A New York investor has acquired 31% of Plaza Communications Inc., an Irvine 
financial publishing concern. Theodore L. Cross, a New York publisher of legal 
textbooks, increased his stake in Plaza from 26% to 31% during the fourth 
quarter ended Oct. 31, 1988, according to documents filed with the Securities 
and Exchange Commission. Tolman Geffs, Plaza Communications chief executive and 
founder, controls 51% of the company's stock. Plaza Communications publishes 
Personal Investor, a monthly magazine with 119,000 subscribers, and Registered 
Representative, a trade magazine distributed to stock brokers. Last year the 
company earned $151,000 on sales of $1.5 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
